Package de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.junit.engine.annotation.extension

Interface ExtensionProvider

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MethodBasedProvider<List<Extension>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstructorBasedExtensionProvider
    public interface ExtensionProvider
extends MethodBasedProvider<List<Extension>>
    An ExtensionProvider is responsible for providing an arbitrary number of Extension implementations (even none is allowed) for a CombinatorialTest.

    To register a ExtensionProvider, use the ExtensionSource annotation as demonstrated by EnableExtension.

    Implementations must provide a no-args constructor.

    This is more or less a copy of org.junit.jupiter.params.provider.ArgumentsProvider from the junit-jupiter-params project.
